net.sf.tweety.logics.cl.kappa

Interface KappaTerm

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    KappaMin, KappaSum, KappaValue

    public interface KappaTerm
    This interface defines a kappa term, that can be evaluated, it can return its value, which is -1 as long as the kappa-term cannot be evaluated and it can return a value for that we know that the kappa-term value is greatar or equal to that value.
    Author:
    Tim Janus

    • Method Detail

      • evaluate

        boolean evaluate()
        Tries to evaluate the kappa term, if the evaluation is successful then the next call of value returns the evaluated value.
        Returns:
        True if the evaluation is sucessful, false otherwise

      • value

        int value()
        Returns:
        The value of this kappa term or -1 if the kappa-term's evaluate() method returns false.

      • greaterEqualThan

        int greaterEqualThan()
        Returns:
        The minimum value of this kappa term, such that the caller knows the kappa term is greater or equal the returned value.

      • getSubTerms

        Set<KappaTerm> getSubTerms()
        Processes all the sub-terms
        Returns:
        A set containing all the sub-terms of the kappa term
